        "section_title": "",
        "section_sub": "Antúnio Mello is a 25-year-old surfboard shaper from Lisbon who owns his own business and space where he creates amazing surfboards. In this interview, he shares his experience as a Paez face and how he integrates creativity into his daily life. He talks about the intersection of surf culture and Paez, his approach to surfboard design, and the balance between his professional and personal life.António also shares his memorable surfing experiences and what distinguishes his surfboards from others on the market.",
        "description": "",
        "section_url": ""
      }
    },
    "22e08688-59e1-4526-8636-626c0b3bff2d": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "e184a178-350f-4c09-a2db-6548babd2b08": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><em><strong>Q: What convinced you to become the face of Paez in 2023, and what do you love most about the brand?</strong></em></p><p><br/><strong>A: </strong>When you guys approached me, I immediately said yes. I'm not one to runaway from these types of invitations. But basically I identify with the brand, I've been a customer for years now.</p><p><em><strong><br/>Q: We know you're a big fan of Paez, but can you share a specific memory or experience that solidified your love for the brand?</strong></em></p><p><br/><strong>A:</strong> Absolutely! One year, I bought a pair of nautical-style cloth shoes from Paez and wore them non-stop throughout the entire year. I even wore them for skateboarding! They were so comfortable and durable that I couldn't bear to part with them.<br/>That experience cemented my love for the brand, and I've been a loyal fan ever since.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
