    "7208b273-2a0b-4e3c-b889-495373e38785": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "5e7056a2-91a0-46b2-a87a-dacbc730dea0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><em><strong>Q: Paez's motto is all about \"walking the talk.\" How do you embody this in your everyday life, and do you have any personal mottos or guiding principles.</strong></em></p><p><br/><strong>A: </strong>For me, walking the talk means being authentic and true to yourself. I try to embody this by staying true to my values and beliefs, even in the face of challenges or opposition. One personal motto that guides me is \"no regrets.\" I always strive to live in the moment and pursue my passions without fear or hesitation</p><p><em><strong><br/>Q: How do you think Paez captures the essence of surf culture, and what makes it so appealing to surfers and beach goers?</strong></em></p><p><br/><strong>A:</strong> Paez and surf culture intersect in many ways- the product is perfect for a day at the beach, it's easy to wear (you pull them on and off), and then I think a lot it's in the vibe of Paez- it's cool and laid-back, which every surfer can connect and embodies fun times at the beach.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
