    "175b2f9b-109f-4f10-b9e9-49ac1ea3e2b4": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "679594a5-6bfe-4c89-be15-40da5c588b5d": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><em><strong>Q: Can you tell us a bit about your journey into surfboard shaping and how it has impacted your life?</strong></em></p><p><br/><strong>A: </strong>I've always been drawn to building and creating things with my own hands, and when I started surfing, I became fascinated by the art and skill of surfboard shaping. It's a challenging and rewarding process that requires both a technical approach and a creative vision. Surfboard shaping has not only allowed me to pursue my passion for surfing but has also given me a sense of purpose and fulfillment in my work.</p><p><em><strong><br/>Q: </strong></em><strong>Can you share a particularly memorable surfing experience and how it has impacted you?</strong></p><p><br/><strong>A:</strong> One of my most memorable surfing experiences was when I tried a new board design and was blown away by how it felt in the water. It was a moment of pure joy and excitement, and it made me realize the power of innovation and experimentation in shaping, That experience has inspired me to continue pushing the boundaries of surfboard design and to always be open to new ideas and possibilities.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
